BBNAIJA 6 runner-up, Liquorose and Mavins signee, Ruger, have secured ambassadorial roles with beer brand, Tiger beer. Liquorose and Ruger join five ambassadors that were unveiled by the beer brand in a private event recently. The BBNaija star expressed delight at the new role saying she would give her best to represent the brand and meet all expectations as required by the brand. In the same vein, Ruger stressed that the deal is a good sign for his career  which has since taken flight since he broke out.   OT Bolts premieres Rising Sun, bags endorsement deal     ONYEKA ONWENU: I see my children as prized possession     Omo Tosan takes Koredianx high up music charts   Read Also: OT Bolts premieres Rising Sun, bags endorsement deal Other ambassadors of the brand include award-winning alternative duo, The Cavemen, and fashion face, Noble Igwe. Speaking on the new Tiger ambassadors, the Senior Brand Manager, Tiger Beer, Nigerian Breweries Plc, Beatrice Adeniran expressed her excitement. “We are delighted to reveal these five bold mavericks who, against the obstacles in our society, have charted their own course and found their unique voices. Their journey depicts what living uncaged truly means and this event is to celebrate them and recognize them for their courage and unrelenting drive.”